{
  "texts": [
    "The NMI is used to measure the similarity between two clustering results, namely the predefined cell-type labels and the clustering result obtained from the embeddings or the graph.",
    "Optimized Louvain clustering is used here according to scIB.",
    "The NMI scores are scaled to [0, 1], where 0 and 1 correspond to uncorrelated clustering and a perfect match, respectively.",
    "The ARI also measures the overlap of two clustering results.",
    "The Rand index (RI 66) considers not only cell pairs that are assigned in the same clusters but also ones in different clusters in the predicted (Louvain clustering) and true (cell-type) clusters."
  ]
}